  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime of $25,000, a portion of which has already been restituted. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the sentencing guidelines for a first-time, non-violent offender of this magnitude generally lean toward shorter custodial sentences or community-based alternatives rather than the extreme 10-year demand shouted by the spectator, which is disregarded as it lacks legal basis. Considering the full circumstances, 6 months is an appropriate term to serve as a deterrent and punishment while acknowledging the defendant's lack of prior criminal history and partial restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
